\begin{abstract}
We study four-terminal junction of spinless Luttinger liquid wires, which is equivalent to corner junction of two helical edges states of topological insulators.  
We use the fermionic representation and the scattering state formalism, in order to compute the renormalization group (RG) equations for the linear response conductances. 
First we  analyze the symmetric setup considered previously and find a correspondence between the earlier studies and our approach. Next we consider  a general junction of non-equivalent edge states, allowing different interaction  in them.  Finally we consider the case of  tunneling from the tip of the spinful wire to the edge state which is equally well described in our formalism. 
 In the latter case we  demonstrate the existence of fixed lines in the plane of renormalized conductances,  
 in addition to a conventional fixed point of RG equations.   The scaling exponents and phase portraits are obtained in all cases. 
\end{abstract}

